	"metadata": {
		"title": "kernel: ppp: reject claimed-as-LCP but actually malformed packets (moderate)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-41044",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-41044",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: The MITRE CVE dictionary describes this issue as: In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nppp: reject claimed-as-LCP but actually malformed packets\n\nSince 'ppp_async_encode()' assumes valid LCP packets (with code\nfrom 1 to 7 inclusive), add 'ppp_check_packet()' to ensure that\nLCP packet has an actual body beyond PPP_LCP header bytes, and\nreject claimed-as-LCP but actually malformed data otherwise.",
